The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 August is 2,872 (332.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 16 August, there were 33 new confirmed cases (3.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 09 August, there were 19 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 74% (14 extra cases).
